{
  "primary_issue": "Unbounded memory growth due to StringBuilder accumulation of user input across requests.",
  "evidence": "The instance variable `requestAudit` (StringBuilder) is shared across all requests to this servlet. Each call to doPost appends the current timestamp and the user-controlled `op` parameter without any size limit. Over time, this will cause the StringBuilder to grow indefinitely, leading to OutOfMemoryError.",
  "fix_summary": "Remove the instance-level StringBuilder or limit its size. For auditing, write to a file or database with rotation, or use a bounded data structure (e.g., a ring buffer). Alternatively, do not store audit data in memory across requests."
}
